{"source_url": "https://www.instagram.com/ukraine_brief/reel/DZ_-IqzCGj5/", "scraped_at": "2026-06-26T23:21:42.973924+00:00", "id": "DZ_-IqzCGj5", "description": "Dnipro: Another Forced Conscription Incident Caught on Camera?\n\nA new video from Dnipro shows several men in military-style uniforms pulling a civilian away from a public minibus stop and forcing him toward a waiting van. The man can be heard calling for help as bystanders attempt to intervene.\n\nAccording to the footage, several people tried to open the van's door and assist the man, but were pushed back by the uniformed individuals. Moments later, the van left the scene with the civilian inside.\n\nThe incident has drawn additional scrutiny due to the apparent lack of police involvement. Legal experts and activists have repeatedly noted that military personnel are not empowered to independently apprehend civilians, making such scenes a continuing source of public controversy.\n\nDespite repeated promises of reform and greater transparency, videos of controversial street mobilization incidents continue to surface across the country. No official comments regarding the incident have been released at the time of publication.\n\n#Ukraine #Dnipro #Mobilization #Conscription #MilitaryService #HumanRights #TCC #UkraineNews #BreakingNews #UkraineBrief #News #DniproNews #WarInUkraine #UkraineUpdates #CurrentEvents #EasternEurope #ViralVideo #LawAndOrder #MilitaryRecruitment #UkraineWarNews #PathToEU #EUStandards #UkraineEU #DniproCity #RuleOfLaw #CivilRights #EuropeValues #Transparency #PublicAccountability", "created_at": null, "author": {"id": null, "unique_id": "ukraine_brief", "nickname": "@ukraine_brief", "verified": null, "signature": null, "followers": null, "following": null, "likes": null, "videos": null}, "stats": {"plays": null, "likes": 660, "comments": 128, "shares": null, "saves": null}, "video": {"duration": null, "ratio": null, "cover": "https://scontent-iev1-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/72